Vegetarian "Fish Sauce"
  --Cook's Illustrated

3 c water
1/4 oz dried sliced shiitake mushrooms
3 tbsp salt
2 tbsp shoyu

In a saucepan, simmer all ingredients over medium heat until reduced by half. Strain, cool, and store in the fridge for up to three weeks.



Version from MinimalistBaker
1 1/4 c water
1/4 c dulse loosely packed
1/4 c dried shiitake mushrooms
2 tsp sea salt
1 1/2 tsp chickpea miso (or soy)
1-2 tbsp tamari (or coconut aminos)

To a small saupcepan, add water, dulse, mushrooms, and salt. Bring to a boil, then cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 15-20 min. Remove from heatand let cool slightly. Pour liquid through a fine mesh strainer into a bowl, pressing to squeeze out any remaining liquid. To the bowl add miso and tamari. Taste and adjust as necessary. Store in sealed container in refrigerator for up to 1 month, shake well before use. To freeze, pour into ice cube tray, then store in a freezer safe container for up to 2 months. 

